CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 1, 1960, pg. 1, reads: "'Man of the Hour' - Robert Clemente, Pirates' outfielder and one of the key men in Bucs' championship pennant drive, is the center of jubilant fans during victory celebration in downtown Pittsburgh Sunday night. Clemente is expected to be one of the big Pirate threats when the World Series opens against the New York Yankees at Forbes Field next Wednesday afternoon.  He is a deserving MVP candidate. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Pittsburgh Pirates baseball player Roberto Clemente riding in back of car in parade for celebration of 1960 National League Championship, Downtown
